import pandas as pd
import numpy as np

# Calculate correlation matrix
corr_matrix = df.corr().abs()

# Select upper triangle of correlation matrix
upper = corr_matrix.where(np.triu(np.ones(corr_matrix.shape), k=1).astype(bool))

# Find features with correlation greater than 0.7
threshold = 0.7
high_corr = [column for column in upper.columns if any(upper[column] > threshold)]

# Print highly correlated features
print("Highly correlated features:", high_corr)

# Drop highly correlated features
df_new = df.drop(high_corr, axis=1)

Random Forest Classifier¶

In [10]:
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score, precision_score, recall_score, f1_score, confusion_matrix, cohen_kappa_score, matthews_corrcoef, roc_auc_score
from sklearn.preprocessing import LabelEncoder

# Fit random forest classifier model
rfc = RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=100, max_depth=10, random_state=10)
rfc.fit(X_train, y_train)

# Predict on test data
y_pred = rfc.predict(X_test)

# Encode the string labels as numeric values
le = LabelEncoder()
y_test_encoded = le.fit_transform(y_test)
y_pred_encoded = le.transform(y_pred)

# Calculate evaluation metrics
accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)
precision = precision_score(y_test, y_pred, pos_label='Pass')
recall = recall_score(y_test, y_pred, pos_label='Pass')
f1 = f1_score(y_test, y_pred, pos_label='Pass')
kappa = cohen_kappa_score(y_test, y_pred)
mcc = matthews_corrcoef(y_test, y_pred)
auc = roc_auc_score(y_test_encoded, y_pred_encoded)
cm = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred, labels=['Fail', 'Pass'])

# Print results
print("Accuracy:", accuracy)
print("Precision:", precision)
print("Recall:", recall)
print("F1 score:", f1)
print("Kappa:", kappa)
print("MCC:", mcc)
print("AUC:", auc)
print("Confusion matrix:\n", cm)

Feature Importance¶

In [13]:
import numpy as np
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier, GradientBoostingClassifier
from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier

# Train the models
rfc.fit(X_train, y_train)
gbc.fit(X_train, y_train)

# Get the feature importances
importances_rfc = rfc.feature_importances_
importances_gbc = gbc.feature_importances_

# Sort the features by importance
indices_rfc = np.argsort(importances_rfc)[::-1]
indices_gbc = np.argsort(importances_gbc)[::-1]

# Print the feature rankings for each model
print("Random Forest feature ranking:")
for f in range(X.shape[1]):
    print("%d. %s (%f)" % (f + 1, X.columns[indices_rfc[f]], importances_rfc[indices_rfc[f]]))
print("\n")

print("Gradient Boosting feature ranking:")
for f in range(X.shape[1]):
    print("%d. %s (%f)" % (f + 1, X.columns[indices_gbc[f]], importances_gbc[indices_gbc[f]]))
print("\n")

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier
from sklearn.ensemble import GradientBoostingClassifier
from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier

# Access feature importance
rfc_importance = rfc.feature_importances_
gbc_importance = gbc.feature_importances_

# Plot feature importance side by side
fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(ncols=2, figsize=(18, 12))

ax1.barh(X_train.columns, rfc_importance)
ax1.set_title('Random Forest Classifier Feature Importance')
ax1.set_xlabel('Importance')
ax1.set_ylabel('Feature')

ax2.barh(X_train.columns, gbc_importance)
ax2.set_title('Gradient Boosting Classifier Feature Importance')
ax2.set_xlabel('Importance')
ax2.set_ylabel('Feature')

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

ROC Curves Graph¶

In [18]:
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier, GradientBoostingClassifier
from sklearn.neighbors import KNeighborsClassifier
from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier
from sklearn.metrics import roc_curve, auc
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt


# Define your target variable
target_col = 'final_result'

# Define your features
feature_cols = [col for col in df_new.columns if col not in ['id_student', target_col]]

# Split your data into training and testing sets
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(df_new[feature_cols], df_new[target_col], test_size=0.3, random_state=42)

# Define your models
models = {
    'Random Forest': RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=100, max_depth=5),
    'Gradient Boosting': GradientBoostingClassifier(n_estimators=100, max_depth=5),
    'K-Neighbors': KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors=5),
}

# Calculate and plot ROC curves for each model
plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
for name, model in models.items():
    model.fit(X_train, y_train)
    if hasattr(model, "decision_function"):
        y_score = model.decision_function(X_test)
    else:
        y_score = model.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1]
    fpr, tpr, _ = roc_curve(y_test, y_score, pos_label='Pass')
    roc_auc = auc(fpr, tpr)
    plt.plot(fpr, tpr, label=f'{name} (AUC = {roc_auc:.2f})')
    
# Add a diagonal line for reference
plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], linestyle='--', color='black')

# Add labels and legend
plt.xlabel('False Positive Rate')
plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate')
plt.title('ROC Curves')
plt.legend(loc='lower right')
plt.show()

In [20]:
model_rfc = RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=100, max_depth=5)

# Generate learning curve data
train_sizes, train_scores, test_scores = learning_curve(model_rfc, X, y, cv=10, scoring='accuracy', n_jobs=-1)

# Calculate mean and standard deviation of train and test scores
train_scores_mean = np.mean(train_scores, axis=1)
train_scores_std = np.std(train_scores, axis=1)
test_scores_mean = np.mean(test_scores, axis=1)
test_scores_std = np.std(test_scores, axis=1)

# Plot learning curve
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.plot(train_sizes, train_scores_mean, 'o-', color='r', label='Training score')
plt.plot(train_sizes, test_scores_mean, 'o-', color='g', label='Cross-validation score')
plt.fill_between(train_sizes, train_scores_mean - train_scores_std,
                 train_scores_mean + train_scores_std, alpha=0.1, color='r')
plt.fill_between(train_sizes, test_scores_mean - test_scores_std,
                 test_scores_mean + test_scores_std, alpha=0.1, color='g')
plt.xlabel('Training Set Size')
plt.ylabel('Accuracy Score')
plt.legend(loc='best')
plt.title('Random Forest Learning Curve')
plt.show()
